good recipe for french silk pie i've done a search for recipes and tried a few but i end up with the same problem every time the flavor is good but the sugar does not dissolve so the end result is a very grainy sugary filling does anyone have a good french silk pie recipe that is not grainy thanks cup whipping cream ounce package semisweet chocolate pieces cup butter cup granulated sugar beaten egg yolks tablespoons creme de cacao or whipping cream baked or inch pastry shell whipped cream optional chocolate curls or miniature chocolate pieces optional in a heavy quart saucepan combine the cup whipping cream chocolate pieces butter and sugar cook over low heat stirring constantly until chocolate is melted this should take about minutes remove saucepan from heat gradually stir about half of the hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks return egg mixture to saucepan cook over medium low heat stirring constantly until mixture is slightly thickened and nearly bubbly this should take to minutes remove saucepan from heat mixture may appear to separate stir in creme de cacao or whipping cream place saucepan in a bowl of ice water stir occasionally until mixture stiffens and becomes hard to stir minutes transfer chocolate mixture to a medium mixing bowl beat the cooled chocolate mixture with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for to minutes or until light and fluffy spread filling in a baked pastry shell cover and chill pie about hours or until set or for up to hours at serving time top each serving with whipped cream and sprinkle with chocolate curls or pieces if desired Chocolate Bread Breakfast Tea Mayonnaise Cream (food) Japanese cuisine Cookware and bakeware Cuisine of Denmark Tofu Cold Stone Creamery Turkish Delight Halva Dairy Custard Cuisine of Brazil Pancake Cake Cocoa Oreo Souffl__ Roux Baked Alaska Bagel Cookie Carbon dioxide Rice pudding Idli French fries Pizza Recipe Chili con carne Barbecue Puff pastry Gumbo Honey Brewery Pie Bacon Potato Hot chocolate Appl